+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.302.3","title":"[audit][plan] Make obligation safety summaries reflect leak analysis","description":"src/plan/analysis.rs currently reports raw obligation safety enums without deriving fail-closed leak risk from ObligationFlow. That lets nodes with cancel leaks or unresolved must-resolve paths look safe in summaries and side-condition checks. Scope: derive effective obligation safety from flow data, use it in node/project summaries and rewrite safety checks, add focused regressions, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/test commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaDeer","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:43:17.901153273Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:43:17.901153273Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.302.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:43:17.901153273Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.302.4","title":"[audit][record] Make SymbolObligationTracker registration fail closed on duplicate IDs and wrong-region obligations","description":"src/record/symbol_obligation_tracker.rs currently lets register() silently replace an existing obligation with the same ObligationId and never validates that the obligation belongs to the tracker's region. That can discard a still-pending obligation without a terminal transition and can hide cross-region obligations under the wrong region tracker. Scope: make registration reject or fail closed on duplicate pending IDs and wrong-region obligations, add focused regressions, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/test commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaDeer","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-13T06:44:36.021902549Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:44:36.021902549Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.302.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:44:36.021902549Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.302.5","title":"[audit][record] Reject cross-region SymbolObligationTracker registrations","description":"src/record/symbol_obligation_tracker.rs currently accepts SymbolObligation values from any owning region, even though the tracker itself is region-scoped. That lets a region tracker silently adopt another region's obligation record, undermining region ownership, leak accounting, and close-to-quiescence invariants. Make registration fail closed when obligation.inner.region does not match tracker.region_id, keep indexing behavior unchanged for valid obligations, add a focused regression, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/test commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaDeer","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:45:30.520016957Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:45:30.520016957Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.302.5","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:45:30.520016957Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.303","title":"Batch 301: 6 io/ext + copy + lines files audited — all SOUND, zero bugs. Files: src/io/ext/mod.rs (29L), src/io/ext/seek_ext.rs (203L), src/io/ext/read_ext.rs (~36KB), src/io/ext/write_ext.rs (~25KB), src/io/copy.rs (~44KB), src/io/lines.rs (219L). Key patterns: completed flags on all futures, cooperative yield counters (>32), fail-closed repoll guards, incremental UTF-8 validation in ReadToString, CopyBuf un-marks completed if final flush pending.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"BoldStream","created_at":"2026-03-13T01:44:47.270144992Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:01:43.058570093Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:01:43.058548212Z","close_reason":"Closed as verified stale-open SOUND batch. Spot-check confirmed the recorded invariants still hold across the cited surfaces: src/io/lines.rs has a completed latch and safe post-completion None returns; src/io/copy.rs and CopyBuf carry completed-state fail-closed guards, including the branch that clears completed when final flush remains pending; src/io/ext/read_ext.rs, write_ext.rs, and seek_ext.rs all retain completed flags with explicit post-completion error returns. Validation in this pass: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/io/ext/mod.rs src/io/ext/seek_ext.rs src/io/ext/read_ext.rs src/io/ext/write_ext.rs src/io/copy.rs src/io/lines.rs passed. No code changes were needed; this closes stale backlog bookkeeping only.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.303","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T01:44:47.270144992Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.304","title":"Batch 302: 7 io files audited — all SOUND, zero bugs. Files: src/io/cap.rs (2826L), src/io/read.rs (410L), src/io/read_buf.rs (91L), src/io/seek.rs (53L), src/io/split.rs (344L), src/io/write.rs (408L), src/io/mod.rs (105L). Key patterns: capability-based default-deny authority system with 6 IoCap sub-traits, builder dedup guards, Chain reads avoid false EOF on full buffer, Take limit uses saturating_sub, RefCell-based read/write split.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"WindyDesert","created_at":"2026-03-13T01:46:06.590577574Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:09:40.089931182Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:09:40.071585962Z","close_reason":"Verified stale-open SOUND batch. Manual audit confirmed the recorded invariants still hold in src/io/cap.rs, src/io/read.rs, src/io/read_buf.rs, src/io/seek.rs, src/io/split.rs, src/io/write.rs, and src/io/mod.rs: capability authorities remain default-deny with deduped grant builders; Chain avoids false EOF on full buffers; Take uses saturating_sub for remaining limit; split halves remain RefCell-backed borrowing wrappers without hidden ownership transfer. Validation in this pass: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check on the claimed files passed; UBS scan on src/io produced no concrete findings in the claimed files beyond generic test/library inventory; rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-windydesert-304 cargo test --lib io:: -- --nocapture reached an unrelated repo-wide compile failure in src/net/websocket/client.rs (missing Cx::now()), not this audit surface.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.304","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T01:46:06.590577574Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
